docs.abstract: Raymond Buckley, the chairman of the New Hampshire Democratic Party, talks about Pete Buttigieg and what it means to be gay and married and running for president in 2019.
docs.snippet: Raymond Buckley, the chairman of the New Hampshire Democratic Party, talks about Pete Buttigieg and what it means to be gay and married and running for president in 2019.
docs.lead_paragraph: In 2009, Raymond Buckley was the only openly gay state chairman in the Democratic Party. His state, New Hampshire, was one of very few that had passed a law making same-sex marriages legal. Barack Obama, the new president, held a position that was then the norm for Democratic politicians: that marriage should be reserved for heterosexuals.

headline.main: Is America Ready for a Gay President? ‘You’re Going to See the Wall Crumble’
headline.print_headline: Can a Gay Candidate  Win the Presidency? As Much ‘as Anyone’
